  <zone type="main">
    <line>Chapter 10<hi rend="underline">th</hi></line>
    <milestone unit="tei:p"/>
    <line>Night had closed <mod type="additions"><add place="sublinear">&#x2038;</add><add place="superlinear">in</add></mod> when I arrived <del
        rend="strikethrough">and</del></line>
    <line>the gates of Geneva were already <mod type="subst"><del rend="strikethrough"
          >closed</del><add place="sublinear">&#x2038;</add><add place="superlinear"
        >shut</add></mod> and</line>
    <line>I determined to remain that night at</line>
    <line>Secheron <add precision="unknown"><ptr target="#c56-0081.01"/></add>. The <mod
        type="subst"><del rend="strikethrough">night</del><add resp="#pbs" place="superlinear"
          >sky</add> was <del rend="strikethrough">very fine</del><add resp="#pbs"
          place="superlinear">serene</add></mod> and</line>
    <line><del rend="strikethrough">unable</del> as I was unable to rest I resolved</line>
    <line>to <mod type="subst"><del rend="strikethrough">walk towards</del><add resp="#pbs"
          place="superlinear">visit</add></mod> the spot where m<add resp="#pbs" place="intralinear"
        >y</add></line>
    <line>poor William had been murdered;</line>
    <line>as I walked I perceived a storm collecting</line>
    <line>on the other side of the lake. I saw the</line>
    <line>lightnings play in the most beautiful</line>
    <line>figures and gained a summit</line>
    <line>that I might observe <del rend="strikethrough">the</del><add place="sublinear"
        >&#x2038;</add><add place="superlinear">its</add> progress.</line>
    <line>It advanced <del rend="strikethrough">slowly and</del> and I soon felt</line>
    <line>the rain coming slowly in large</line>
    <line>drops but its violence quickly encreased.</line>
    <milestone unit="tei:p"/>
    <line>I quitted my seat and walk on,</line>
    <line>although the darkness and storm aug</line>
    <line>mented every minute and the thunder</line>
    <line>burst <del rend="strikethrough">violently over</del> with a terrific</line>
    <line>crash over my head – <delSpan spanTo="#c56-0081.03"/>William I ex</line>
    <line>cried aloud – dear angel this is thy</line>
    <line>funeral this thy dirge.<anchor xml:id="c56-0081.03"/> It was echoed</line>
    <line>from Salêve <mod type="additions" resp="#pbs"><add place="sublinear">&#x2038;</add><add
          place="superlinear">the Jura</add></mod> and the Alps of Savoy–</line>
    <line>vivid flashes of lightning dazzled my</line>
    <line>eyes, <del rend="strikethrough">and</del> illumin<mod type="subst"><del rend="overwritten"
          unit="chars" extent="unknown"/><add resp="#pbs" place="intralinear">ating</add></mod> the
      lake; <del rend="smear">and</del></line>
    <line>then for an instant every thing</line>
    <line>seemed of a pitchy <mod type="subst"><del rend="strikethrough">black</del><add
          place="sublinear">&#x2038;</add><add place="superlinear">darkness</add></mod>
      <del rend="strikethrough">til</del> untill</line>
    <line>the eye recovered itself from the <mod type="additions"><add place="sublinear"
          >&#x2038;</add><add>preceeding</add></mod> flash.</line>
    <line><del rend="cross-hatch">A</del> The storm as is often the case in</line>
